Stuff that gets you
all the way to Level 10.

13:37.830 --> 13:38.600
Razia?

13:38.600 --> 13:42.600
Well, I don´t want any books
written by white dead men.

13:42.600 --> 13:45.000
With you there, kid,
but unfortunately,

13:45.000 --> 13:48.570
that´s 99% of our reading list.

13:48.570 --> 13:50.200
Ms. Carter, any thoughts?

13:52.970 --> 13:58.100
I´m sure your syllabus is full
of diverse and dynamic texts.

14:00.770 --> 14:03.270
Tell you what.
We give them a go.

14:03.270 --> 14:05.230
And if we can´t find anything

14:05.230 --> 14:09.830
that speaks directly
to your lives, we bin them.

14:09.830 --> 14:10.830
Really, Miss?

14:10.830 --> 14:11.830
Agreed, Ms. Carter?

14:14.830 --> 14:15.830
Mum!

14:15.830 --> 14:17.430
Finally!

14:17.430 --> 14:18.470
Chloe?

14:18.470 --> 14:20.900
I´ve been trying you
like all day.

14:20.900 --> 14:22.830
Answer your phone.

14:26.000 --> 14:27.870
[ All gasping, groaning ]

14:29.970 --> 14:30.830
[ Gags ]

14:30.830 --> 14:33.630
I´m sorry.
I´m so sorry.

14:34.470 --> 14:36.070
The kid´s a racist.

14:36.070 --> 14:37.830
Come on, man.

14:37.830 --> 14:40.500
Loosen up.
I thought it were funny.

14:41.200 --> 14:42.970
-Why you selling bacon crisps!
-Hm?

14:42.970 --> 14:44.000
We can´t eat here, bro.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.270
They sell ´em
at the bloody Lidl, as well,

14:46.270 --> 14:47.830
and your mum´s
always shopping there.

14:47.830 --> 14:50.400
They´ve not been
near a bloody pig.

14:50.400 --> 14:52.670
MISSY: Do I get free stuff,
Mrs. Paracha?

14:52.670 --> 14:56.200
Do I look like charity?
You´re no refugee, you know.

14:56.200 --> 14:59.400
Hey, who´s the fitty
with the braces?

15:00.270 --> 15:04.300
Um, that is Alya´s twin.

15:05.430 --> 15:08.500
Don´t worry.
I don´t go out with schoolboys.

15:08.500 --> 15:10.700
We like real men, don´t we, Nas?

15:11.500 --> 15:12.830
We´re gonna go
to the 6th Form Hub.

15:12.830 --> 15:14.000
You coming, Nas?

15:14.000 --> 15:15.370
Yeah, Amira will be there.

15:27.400 --> 15:29.100
Have an apple, love.

15:29.100 --> 15:30.570
On me.

15:37.000 --> 15:38.830
It´ll settle your tummy.

15:43.070 --> 15:45.500
Are you ready to tell me
what´s going on?

15:48.200 --> 15:49.430
Dad threw me out.

15:51.000 --> 15:52.830
Said it wasn´t working.

15:54.200 --> 15:55.970
Chose Eve over me, Mum.

15:57.670 --> 16:00.070
-So I got an Uber here.
-An Uber?

16:01.030 --> 16:01.970
From Peckham?

16:03.270 --> 16:05.970
You, uh -- You know, um...

16:05.970 --> 16:08.000
-Eve´s pregnant?
-What?

16:08.700 --> 16:10.830
Yeah. No warning.

16:10.830 --> 16:13.670
Just meet your blob
of a sibling.

16:13.670 --> 16:16.000
There´s literally
no room for me there.

16:17.300 --> 16:19.300
My room´s gonna be a nursery.

16:21.830 --> 16:23.500
I´ll sort it.

16:24.200 --> 16:25.830
Call your dad.

16:25.830 --> 16:27.630
We´ll get you back down
to London.

16:30.600 --> 16:32.200
I´ll be back in a minute.

16:34.470 --> 16:36.400
She´s had a fallout
with her dad.

16:36.400 --> 16:39.400
Uh, she´s up from London.
She doesn´t normally do this.

16:39.400 --> 16:41.000
Right.
Can we talk about your work?

16:41.000 --> 16:42.230
Have you got a problem
with my work?

16:43.500 --> 16:45.600
I think you´ve got
issues with authority.

16:45.600 --> 16:47.830
[ Scoffs ]
Power´s gone to your head.

16:47.830 --> 16:49.830
You´re talking about throwing
the classics in the bin!

16:49.830 --> 16:53.000
It´s day one.
Get their attention.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.900
-Give me some credit, Mand.
-You want their attention?

16:54.900 --> 16:56.000
Hit them with facts.

16:56.000 --> 16:58.830
One in three kids from this town
fails GCSE English.

16:58.830 --> 17:01.030
Although you´d know that
if you´d been to the inset day.

17:03.230 --> 17:05.100
She can´t stay here
in that state.

17:27.500 --> 17:29.600
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:31.570 --> 17:32.570
Hiya.

17:36.600 --> 17:38.600
Seriously, what´s so good
about in here?

17:38.600 --> 17:40.200
You´ve got a coffee machine,

17:40.200 --> 17:41.430
which is impressive
and everything,

17:41.430 --> 17:42.670
but it´s still school.

17:44.630 --> 17:45.870
I´m your age.
Don´t worry.

17:45.870 --> 17:47.030
You´ve just all
got to be dead to me

17:47.030 --> 17:48.230
´cause you passed your exams
and that.

17:49.170 --> 17:50.470
NASREEN:
It weren´t her fault.

17:50.470 --> 17:53.000
She´s in our year, really.
She´s just got to retake.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.870
Thank you, Nasreen.
Dead sweet.

17:55.870 --> 17:59.670
Missy Booth, good to see you
in uniform for another year.

17:59.670 --> 18:02.900
Got a thing for it, have you?
You´d be so lucky.

18:04.370 --> 18:06.470
Teachers will be well pleased
to see me talking to you all.

18:06.470 --> 18:08.870
Ain´t that the point in this
school, to make us all friends?

18:12.170 --> 18:13.430
You´re real nice, you.

18:13.430 --> 18:15.600
Loving your friends, Nas.
Not prejudiced or nothing.

18:15.600 --> 18:17.430
-Please.
-Just a bitch, then?

18:17.430 --> 18:18.430
-Missy.
-What?

18:20.470 --> 18:21.100
[ Scoffs ]

18:23.200 --> 18:24.830
Ta for support.

18:29.030 --> 18:30.030
She´s all right, you know.

18:30.030 --> 18:31.430
You just got to
give her a chance.

18:32.970 --> 18:35.400
-Nas, drop the kanjari.
-[ Laughs ]

18:35.400 --> 18:37.470
-That´s really rude.
-Calm down.

18:37.470 --> 18:38.830
Look, if you want to play
with your gori mate,

18:38.830 --> 18:40.000
-we´re not stopping you.
-Oh, my God.

18:42.900 --> 18:44.070
Emma?

18:46.670 --> 18:48.200
There´s a bunch of us
going for a meal later

18:48.200 --> 18:49.470
at the pub if you fancy it.

18:49.470 --> 18:51.870
[ Groans ]
I´ll be on chunder alert.

18:51.870 --> 18:52.970
I heard.

18:52.970 --> 18:54.900
Has anyone not?

18:54.900 --> 18:58.030
Come later if she crashes out.
Everyone´s going, right?

18:58.030 --> 18:59.830
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

19:01.030 --> 19:02.630
Might do.

19:07.200 --> 19:08.470
-See you.
-See you.

19:08.500 --> 19:10.000
-See you.
-See you.

19:15.370 --> 19:18.370
-Takeaway tonight?
-Oh, I´ve got to stay back late.

19:18.370 --> 19:20.400
This budget stuff with Sadiq.

19:20.400 --> 19:23.270
I know. Things will
settle down soon, all right?

19:23.270 --> 19:25.230
There´s a few of them going
for a bite to eat, though.

19:25.230 --> 19:26.900
Will you get them
in a round for me?

19:26.900 --> 19:28.500
It´s not them I want to see.

19:28.500 --> 19:29.830
I know.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.700
I´ll be back soon as I can.

19:31.700 --> 19:33.370
Stop kissing the boss.

19:36.200 --> 19:38.170
[ Animals bleating ]

19:43.700 --> 19:47.000
Oh. Ah.

19:50.830 --> 19:52.470
CHLOE: Why do you still live
in this place?

19:52.470 --> 19:54.570
I mean, why?

19:54.570 --> 19:56.000
I like it.

19:56.000 --> 19:57.430
[ Cellphone rings ]

19:57.430 --> 19:58.670
It´s your dad!

19:58.670 --> 20:00.370
CHLOE:
Oh. He´s just gonna have a go.

20:00.370 --> 20:01.900
Not picked up your calls
all this time?

20:01.900 --> 20:03.430
No.

20:03.430 --> 20:05.630
Then let him ring,
let him wonder where I am.

20:05.630 --> 20:07.170
-He doesn´t --
-Nick.

20:07.170 --> 20:09.670
About time. What the hell
do you think you´re doing?

20:10.270 --> 20:12.200
Chloe´s here in bits
´cause of you.

20:13.300 --> 20:15.400
Of course she´s upset!

20:16.700 --> 20:17.430
What?

20:17.430 --> 20:19.500
Don´t listen to him.
He´s a liar!

20:19.500 --> 20:21.670
-She did?
-Bet it´s not like he said.

20:24.200 --> 20:25.970
Okay. Call you back.

20:27.900 --> 20:29.170
[ Cellphone thuds ]

20:31.700 --> 20:32.700
She tripped.

20:32.700 --> 20:34.300
-Tripped?
-You don´t understand.

20:34.300 --> 20:37.170
They were waiting for me
when I came in,

20:37.170 --> 20:41.400
so pleased with themselves
with this stupid scan photo,

20:41.400 --> 20:43.370
saying I´m selfish
for not being happy for them.

20:43.370 --> 20:46.070
So, you attack her?

20:46.070 --> 20:49.100
She came over,
all hands over me, so I just...

20:49.970 --> 20:50.900
...pushed her off.

20:52.030 --> 20:53.170
Unbelievable.

20:53.170 --> 20:55.830
Mum, she tripped. She´s not --
She´s not hurt or anything.

20:55.830 --> 20:58.170
[ Sighs ]
Stay out my sight, Chloe.

20:58.170 --> 20:59.100
I´m going out.

20:59.100 --> 21:00.730
But -- No, Mum, believe me.

21:00.730 --> 21:02.100
You´re lying!

21:02.100 --> 21:04.430
You lied to me before,
and you´re doing it again.

21:04.430 --> 21:05.170
I didn´t!

21:05.170 --> 21:06.630
And now you expect me to stay in

21:06.630 --> 21:08.670
and nurse you through
your hangover?

21:09.430 --> 21:10.870
Forget it, Chloe.

21:10.870 --> 21:13.000
I´m gonna go home, then.

21:13.000 --> 21:15.030
I´ll book an Uber...again.

21:15.030 --> 21:17.430
Don´t even try it.

21:20.070 --> 21:21.570
I´ll do what I want!

21:24.670 --> 21:26.830
[ Shower running,
upbeat music playing ]

21:28.670 --> 21:31.430
EMMA: Forget it, Chloe.
Your phone´s in here with me!

22:16.470 --> 22:18.470
[ Whooshes, chimes ]

22:20.300 --> 22:21.970
[ Door opens ]

22:23.870 --> 22:25.470
Out.

22:29.170 --> 22:31.070
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

22:38.030 --> 22:39.700
[ Beeping ]

22:39.700 --> 22:41.300
Don´t go away.
Tea´s ready.

22:41.300 --> 22:42.900
Oh, my God.

22:44.630 --> 22:47.030
Have you seen this?
Miss Keane´s boobs!

22:48.270 --> 22:50.830
She must have been hacked.
Do not share that.

22:52.830 --> 22:55.300
NANA: How was school with
all that new lot, then?

22:55.300 --> 22:58.600
Oh, Jordan Wilson insulted
half the school.

22:58.600 --> 22:59.830
Jordan?

22:59.830 --> 23:01.970
That -- That´s not Muslim,
is it?

23:04.030 --> 23:05.230
While you´re up there --

23:05.230 --> 23:07.430
Missy, come here now!

23:10.670 --> 23:11.870
It´s Mum.

23:18.230 --> 23:20.430
MISSY:
Oh, Mum. Not again

23:20.430 --> 23:22.000
HAYLEY:
You´ll have to chuck that duvet.

23:22.000 --> 23:24.430
Don´t know where she´s been
or what she´s been using.

23:25.470 --> 23:26.300
Where you going?

23:26.300 --> 23:28.000
Got to see
if all my stuff´s still there.

23:32.030 --> 23:33.970
Where am I?

23:35.030 --> 23:36.670
You´re home, Mum.

23:38.270 --> 23:39.430
My Missy.

23:40.500 --> 23:42.100
Best girl.

23:42.630 --> 23:45.370
NANA:
Dinner´s getting cold down here.

23:45.370 --> 23:46.500
Is there food going?

23:46.500 --> 23:48.030
Nana can´t know you´re here.

23:48.030 --> 23:51.370
What´s her problem?
I´m clean.

23:55.230 --> 23:56.830
Next door, then?

23:57.900 --> 23:59.670
[ Laughter ]

24:00.630 --> 24:03.630
Oh, I love that joke.

24:05.700 --> 24:08.030
Hey, Steve, did you go
to Pakistan in summer?

24:08.030 --> 24:10.270
No, no.
Mandy, she wouldn´t let me.

24:10.270 --> 24:12.830
But she went with governors
and that, so can understand it.

24:12.830 --> 24:16.230
Can´t believe you let him take
her away with no supervision.

24:16.230 --> 24:17.300
Supervision!

24:17.300 --> 24:18.830
Hey, just saying.

24:18.830 --> 24:21.430
Someone told me Sadiq
runs a mattress company

24:21.430 --> 24:24.030
´cause he´s bedded half
the women in the valley.

24:24.630 --> 24:26.230
Oh.

24:26.230 --> 24:27.570
Okay.

24:27.570 --> 24:28.830
Anyone for pudding?

24:35.070 --> 24:37.230
HAYLEY: "Amazing Grace," Nana.
I´ve got to sing it.

24:37.230 --> 24:38.900
It´s just about to start.

24:38.900 --> 24:40.030
How am I --

24:40.830 --> 24:42.830
How am I gonna know
if I´ve won owt now?

24:42.830 --> 24:44.370
I´ve got to do it
for my assembly.

24:44.370 --> 24:46.030
Assembly?
What you on about?

24:46.030 --> 24:47.670
HAYLEY:
I just want your feedback.

24:48.270 --> 24:51.830
BOTH: [ Off-key ]
♫ Amazing grace ♫

24:51.830 --> 24:55.570
♫ How sweet the sound ♫

24:55.570 --> 24:59.270
-Oh.
-♫ That saved a wretch ♫

24:59.270 --> 25:00.530
♫ Like me ♫

25:00.530 --> 25:02.670
The door´s locked.
Nana´s got the key.

25:02.670 --> 25:04.330
Out the back.

25:04.330 --> 25:07.400
♫ But now I´m found ♫

25:07.400 --> 25:12.900
♫ Was blind and now I see ♫

25:12.900 --> 25:18.430
♫ ´Twas grace that taught
my heart to fear ♫

25:18.430 --> 25:20.070
KANEEZ:
You know you have to stop.

25:20.070 --> 25:22.430
They´re too young
to be dealing with all this.

25:22.430 --> 25:23.870
All what?

25:23.870 --> 25:25.830
It´s good job
there isn´t man in this house.

25:25.830 --> 25:27.170
You know, they wouldn´t
allow you through,

25:27.170 --> 25:28.600
the state that you´re in.

25:29.600 --> 25:31.700
Oh, my God, have you seen this?

25:33.000 --> 25:34.600
Oh, don´t show people that.

25:34.600 --> 25:36.830
It´s all over the Internet.
They have a right to know.

25:36.830 --> 25:38.270
I´m sure she didn´t put it up!

25:38.270 --> 25:40.370
What´s she doing
with a photo like that?

25:40.370 --> 25:43.000
Why are you judging?
Sound like your friends.

25:45.170 --> 25:46.500
Have you got a problem
with them?

25:46.500 --> 25:48.500
They got a problem with me.

25:48.500 --> 25:50.870
Missy, I know Alya
can be a bit --

25:50.870 --> 25:51.870
A bit what?

25:52.600 --> 25:54.300
Why don´t you just
tone it down a bit?

25:54.300 --> 25:56.630
That way, you know, she won´t
have anything to moan about.

25:57.970 --> 25:59.870
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

26:23.430 --> 26:25.030
[ Engine shuts off ]

26:25.030 --> 26:26.870
Armley Prison?

26:27.830 --> 26:29.400
Where did you think I´d gone?

26:31.600 --> 26:34.600
To Burnley
to work for your uncle.

26:35.570 --> 26:37.900
Yeah, I went to Burnley
to work for my uncle.

26:38.700 --> 26:39.870
Come on,
I thought you were smart.

26:39.870 --> 26:42.400
Oh, yeah, smart me.
Smart.

26:43.000 --> 26:44.630
You´ve seen my kid.

26:44.630 --> 26:47.500
[ Laughs ]

26:47.500 --> 26:49.470
I didn´t mean that.
I didn´t!

26:51.100 --> 26:52.970
I was just really young.

26:57.430 --> 26:59.200
It didn´t take you long
to get over me, then, did it?

27:00.900 --> 27:03.530
I heard you had to find Allah
to get over me.

27:05.830 --> 27:07.430
Oh, you heard that, did you?

27:16.900 --> 27:18.500
I´d better go.

27:18.500 --> 27:20.170
Chloe´s in there.

27:23.670 --> 27:25.400
[ Chuckles ]

27:25.400 --> 27:28.670
Anyway, thanks for the lift.

27:29.430 --> 27:31.030
It´s all right.

27:32.900 --> 27:33.970
Night.

27:38.900 --> 27:40.830
[ Engine starts ]

27:52.230 --> 27:54.700
[ Door creaks ]

28:20.670 --> 28:22.830
[ Door closes ]

28:43.030 --> 28:44.430
I could have had
an extra hour in bed.

28:44.430 --> 28:46.200
-Sorry.
-I´m not due in till 10:00.

28:46.200 --> 28:48.500
All right, what do you want me
to do, drive home drunk?

28:48.500 --> 28:50.000
I was being responsible.

28:50.000 --> 28:51.670
You don´t sound
that responsible.

28:51.670 --> 28:54.200
You was out all night
drinking, in school.

28:55.500 --> 28:58.030
You was out all night
drinking with...

28:58.030 --> 28:59.170
Sadiq.

29:02.930 --> 29:04.970
You worry too much.

29:04.970 --> 29:06.430
[ Door opens ]

29:09.400 --> 29:10.900
[ Door closes ]

29:10.900 --> 29:11.700
Oh, my gosh!

29:11.700 --> 29:14.230
Mum, please don´t make me go in.

29:14.230 --> 29:16.070
Mum, please,
my temperature was over 40!

29:16.070 --> 29:17.300
I know.

29:17.300 --> 29:19.670
Because you put your thermometer
next to your cup of tea.

29:19.670 --> 29:21.100
[ Wolf-whistles ]

29:21.100 --> 29:23.070
Ignore him.

29:23.070 --> 29:24.970
Do you have to work today?

29:24.970 --> 29:26.300
Pull a sickie.

29:26.300 --> 29:27.630
Let´s do something together,
me and you.

29:27.630 --> 29:30.170
I can´t just sack off work.

29:32.370 --> 29:34.170
[ Door opens ]

29:34.170 --> 29:35.400
Please?

29:35.400 --> 29:37.870
I know you don´t want
to be here.

29:38.900 --> 29:41.470
But you can´t stay at home
watching telly, Chloe.

29:41.470 --> 29:44.070
It´s GCSE year.
You´ve got to...

29:44.070 --> 29:45.870
keep up.

29:45.870 --> 29:47.400
So, why don´t you get comfy?

29:49.970 --> 29:53.670
And why don´t you lose yourself
out on the wily, windy moors?

29:53.670 --> 29:56.630
I´ll be back, at break.

30:04.030 --> 30:06.470
[ Laughter ]

30:06.470 --> 30:08.500
-I´ll send to you.
-Yeah, send to me.

30:08.500 --> 30:10.030
-Send to me.
-Serious.

30:10.030 --> 30:11.200
I will.

30:11.200 --> 30:13.400
She´s gonna get in trouble
if you shared that.

30:13.400 --> 30:15.570
-I told you.
-ZAIN: Oi, oi, oi, oi, oi!

30:15.570 --> 30:17.300
If this is how she´s gonna
engage us this year...

30:17.300 --> 30:18.430
´Cause I´m up for that!

30:18.430 --> 30:20.230
[ Laughter ]

30:20.230 --> 30:21.270
Morning.

30:21.270 --> 30:22.470
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:22.470 --> 30:25.970
Phones away.
Away with the phones.

30:25.970 --> 30:26.900
Right.

30:26.900 --> 30:32.830
Now we´re gonna find out
what lies underneath it all.

30:32.830 --> 30:35.600
-Adult content, Miss?
-You need a warning sticker!

30:35.600 --> 30:36.670
[ Laughter ]

30:37.670 --> 30:39.400
In your seats.
Come on!

30:39.400 --> 30:43.070
Miss? Miss?
You been on Twitter?

30:43.070 --> 30:44.100
No.

30:45.970 --> 30:47.400
Miss Keane.

30:49.670 --> 30:51.900
Do you always post
your holiday photos online?

30:51.900 --> 30:52.870
I don´t understand.

30:52.870 --> 30:54.170
Have you not got
a password on your phone?

30:54.170 --> 30:56.070
Do you leave your phone out
in class?

30:56.070 --> 30:57.500
[ Scoffs ]

30:59.600 --> 31:01.330
My bloody daughter!

31:01.330 --> 31:02.900
I´ve -- I´ve had parents
ringing me.

31:02.900 --> 31:04.300
I´ve even had staff
coming in here.

31:04.300 --> 31:07.170
-Who?
-I told ´em where to go.

31:07.700 --> 31:08.670
[ Sighs ]

31:08.670 --> 31:10.070
I´ve got a governors´
meeting tonight.

31:10.070 --> 31:11.570
No doubt this will come up.

31:11.570 --> 31:13.570
I mean, I already had to
talk about Jordan Wilson.

31:13.570 --> 31:14.900
-Now this.
-The governors?

31:14.900 --> 31:16.830
-You´re joking!
